Let $r_1$ and $r_2$ be the radii of the two circular faces. <solution>Given: The slant height ($L$) of the frustum is 8 cm and the distance between the centers of the two circles is 15 cm. Using Pythagoras theorem , 
\begin{align*}
r_1^2 + L^2 &= (10 - 8)^2 \\ & \ \\
r_1^2 + 64 &= 4 \\  & \ \\
r_1^2 &= -60  \\ 
\end{align*} 
We cannot have a negative number for radius, so we made a mistake. The actual distance between the two points from two lines is 8 cm, and we used $15 + 8$.
