\begin{align*}
S &= \pi r_1 L + \pi r_2 L + \pi(r_1 + r_2)L   \\   & \ \\
S &=  \pi \times 0 \times 8 + \pi \times 10 \times 8 + \pi \times (0 + 10) 8   \\ &&   & \ \\
S &= \boxed{160 \pi } \,\,\,\, square \,\,\, cm.
\end{align*}  

The lateral surface area is $\pi(r_1+r_2)L$, where $r_1$ and $r_2$ are the radii of the two circular faces, and $L$ is the slant height. Given $r_1=0$, $r_2=10$, and $L=8$, the lateral surface area is $\pi(0+10)8=\boxed{80\pi}$ square cm. To find the total surface area, we need to add the area of the two circular faces, which is $\pi r_1^2+\pi r_2^2=\pi(0)^2+\pi(10)^2=\boxed{100\pi}$ square cm. The total surface area of the frustum is $\boxed{180\pi}$ square cm. Note that the given diagram shows the entire frustum, not just the lateral surface area.

